        "content": "<p>angelnereira opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13472\">PR #13472</a> from <code>angelnereira:gc-funcref-type-check-bail</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2>Summary</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Replace the GC funcref table subtype assertion with bail_bug so corrupted funcref table IDs are reported as controlled internal errors instead of panicking in release builds.</li>\n<li>Add a focused regression test for mismatched typed funcref table lookups.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Context</h2>\n<p>This follows the defense-in-depth direction discussed in #13216: GC heap corruption checks should prefer controlled internal errors where the surrounding code can already return Result.</p>\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>cargo fmt --all -- --check</li>\n<li>cargo check -p wasmtime</li>\n<li>cargo test -p wasmtime typed_get_rejects_mismatched_func_type</li>\n<li>git diff --check</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>",
